Bolitoglossa cathyledecae
is easily distinguishable by its unique coloration (pinkish flesh with flame scarlet speckles and ventral salmon color) from the large black salamanders found between Costa Rica and Panamá , including the almost entirely black species
B. anthracina Brame, Savage
, Wake and Hanken;
B. compacta
Wake , Brame and Duellman;
B. copia
Wake , Hanken and Ibañez;
B. magnifica Hanken
, Wake and Savage;
B. nigrescens Taylor
;
B. robusta Cope
; and
B. sombra Hanken
, Wake and Savage.

