subSubSection.paragraph:
Taxonomic work is still needed in the highlands between Costa Rica and Panamá (
Garcia-Paris et al. 2008
;
Bolaños and Wake 2009
; Boza-Oviedo et al. 2012; Kubicki and Arias 2016 ), with vast remote areas still unexplored, mainly along the Serranía de Talamanca. Cloud forests are vulnerable to climate change due to the low range of mobility of the upper highland endemic species (
Davies et al. 2004
;
Paaijmans et al. 2013
). Consequently, species or populations restricted to such habitats are enormously susceptible to slight changes in the environment and thus face an elevated risk of extinction (Batista et al. 2020). An urgent conservation plan is required to protect the surrounding cloudforest and the entire La Amistad International Park to preserve its unique pool of endemic species.
